=== 評價 ===
[[爛番茄|爛番茄]]新鮮度30%，基於290條評論，平均分為5/10<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/passengers_2016 |title=Passengers (2016) |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=2016-12-15 |archive-date=2016-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161218173331/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/passengers_2016 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]得分41，評價以負面居多<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/passengers-2016 |title=Passengers reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic|Metacritic]] |accessdate=2016-12-15 |archive-date=2020-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201115072445/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/passengers-2016 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[影院评分|影院评分]]根据影迷投票打出B的[[平均数|平均]]分（评分范围为A+到F）<ref name="CinemaScore">{{cite web |url=https://m.cinemascore.com |title=CinemaScore |work=cinemascore.com |accessdate=2020-10-12 |archive-date=2019-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210223808/https://m.cinemascore.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[互联网电影数据库|IMDb]]則獲得7.0/10的普遍好評。

多位影评人批评吉姆决定唤醒休眠中的旅客陪伴自己的核心剧情点有悖于伦理道德。《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》的丽贝卡·霍肯斯（{{lang|en|Rebecca Hawkes}}）称电影毫无浪漫可言，反而是一场“令人不寒而栗的操纵”，称此种行为是“暴力中心行为”，被软化且合乎情理，道德上类似于《[[星际穿越|星际穿越]]》中的罪犯化身为反派<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2016/12/16/chris-pratt-jennifer-lawrences-passengers-isnt-romance-creepy/|title=Chris Pratt and Jennifer Lawrence's Passengers isn't a romance: it's a creepy ode to manipulation|newspaper=The Telegraph|access-date=2016-12-29|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116083442/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2016/12/16/chris-pratt-jennifer-lawrences-passengers-isnt-romance-creepy/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。霍肯斯和《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》的保罗·塔西（{{lang|en|Paul Tassi}}）都表示宣传团队在预告片中故意隐瞒奥罗拉苏醒的原因<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/insertcoin/2016/12/24/the-passengers-trailers-all-hid-a-twist-that-ruins-the-movie-from-the-start/#4a0d455c73b6|title=The 'Passengers' Trailers All Hid A Twist That Ruins The Movie From The Start|last=Tassi|first=Paul|newspaper=[[Forbes|Forbes]]|access-date=2016-12-29|archive-date=2020-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123230345/https://www.forbes.com/sites/insertcoin/2016/12/24/the-passengers-trailers-all-hid-a-twist-that-ruins-the-movie-from-the-start/#4a0d455c73b6|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《[[卫报|卫报]]》的安德鲁·普耳弗（{{lang|en|Andrew Pulver}}）称电影是“《[[星際穿越|星際效應]]》版的社交媒体跟踪”，“开头令人毛骨悚然”，背离了爱情喜剧片想方设法“降落”的狡猾缠扰战术，片子“可怕却不可避免”<ref name="Guardian" />。Vox的阿丽莎·威尔金逊（{{lang|en|Alissa Wilkinson}}）称影片是“[[斯德哥尔摩综合症|斯德哥尔摩综合症]]的妄想，被抓者最终发现乃至爱上抓自己的人”，“实在是个令人不安的实现妄想的愿望”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vox.com/culture/2016/12/21/14005762/passengers-review-spoilers-jennifer-lawrence-chris-pratt|title=Passengers is 3 movies in one, each creepier than the last|last=Wilkinson|first=Alissa|newspaper=Vox|access-date=2016-12-29|archive-date=2020-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120193710/https://www.vox.com/culture/2016/12/21/14005762/passengers-review-spoilers-jennifer-lawrence-chris-pratt|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

